OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FIndia's unwinnable battle  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fagainst spitting           
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Earlier this year, Raja and Priti      
OL,6, Narasimhan kicked off a road trip      
OL,7, across India armed with one message:   
OL,8, stop spitting in public. The couple    
OL,9, carried a loudspeaker and blared their 
OL,10, message from inside a car covered in   
OL,11, anti-spitting slogans.                 
OL,13,FIf you have spent time in India, you   
OL,14,Fknow what the Narasimhans are up       
OL,15,Fagainst. Saliva graces the streets.    
OL,16,FSometimes plain and phlegmy, sometimes 
OL,17,Fblood red from chewing tobacco-laced   
OL,18,Fbetel nut or paan, it decorates simple 
OL,19,Fwalls and mighty edifices alike. It    
OL,20,Feven threatens Kolkata city's historic 
OL,21,Fhowrah bridge.                         
